               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-272-person2179">
                  JOHN 
                  THORRY
               <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2179" type="surname" value="THORRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2179" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2179" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am one of the watchmen of <placeName id="t18270913-272-crimeloc1532">St. Katherine's Docks</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-272-crimeloc1532" type="placeName" value="St. Katherine's Docks"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-272-crimeloc1532" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-272-off1529 t18270913-272-crimeloc1532"></join>. On the 7th of August, about half-past eight o'clock in the evening, I saw the prisoner taking some lead off a small wash-house; he broke it and doubled it up; I sent for an officer and had him taken - he had removed it from the top to the bottom - it belonged to the Company.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-272-person2180">
                  ROBERT 
                  HENRY BURGESS
               <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2180" type="surname" value="HENRY BURGESS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2180" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2180" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was called by Thorby - we could not see the prisoner; I called for a light, and found him in the adjoining washhouse, and found the lead on the ground; I compared it with the place - it fits exactly with what remains.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-272-person2181">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SITGRAVE
               <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2181" type="surname" value="SITGRAVE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2181" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2181" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am clerk to Messrs. Paulin and Co., who are employed by the St. Katherine's Dock Company - they have been in possession of this house some time - it is in Mablin's-rents, all of which is in the Company's possession; I had possession of the house for them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going into this house to look for my trowel - I had been at work in Burr-street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-272-person2182">
                  JOHN 
                  THORBY
               <interp inst="t18270913-272-person2182" type="surname" value="THORBY"></interp>
